eferred to on the Eqlizer page appears right, the Dual Wield formula is wrong, at least for warriors. The correct formula for Double Attack and Dual Wield for warriors are:<br><br>Chance to Double Attack = (Skill + Level)/500<br>Chance to Dual Wield = (Skill + Level)/400<br><br>This is correct for a warrior, but Rangers may use a different constant for Dual Wield instead of 400. The Ranger who posted on Eqlizer said that this number was actually 600, meaning warriors dual wield 50% more often than Rangers. Anyone have a log they can parse to back up or correct this?<br><br>For more details on this and the data used to derive them, see <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://boards.stratics.com/cgi-bin/boards/eq/showflat.pl?Cat=9&Board=eqwarriors&Number=344003&page=0&view=collapsed&sb=5">boards.stratics.com/cgi-b...apsed&sb=5</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> <br><br>If your interested in a discussion for what the relative weights should be for Min, MN, and Max in determining average damage is <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://pub3.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showMessage?topicID=4624.topic">pub3.ezboard.com/fpaladin...4624.topic</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> <br> <p><BR><BR><BR><img src="http://www.harrythecat.com/graphics/k/knight3.gif" align="center"><img src="http://www.geocities.com/gwlaw99/clipboard2.gif" align="center"> <img src="http://www.harrythecat.com/graphics/k/knight2.gif" align="center"></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathtomesofknowledge.showPrevMessage?topicID=13.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathtomesofknowledge.showNextMessage?topicID=13.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathtomesofknowledge.ema